<title>USA: U.S. HEADLINE STOCKS - Issues to watch - May 22.</title>
<headline>U.S. HEADLINE STOCKS - Issues to watch - May 22.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Stocks to watch this morning:</p>
<p>-- Charter One, the holding company of Charter One Bank, agreed to acquire RCSB Financial Inc, holding company of Rochester Community Savings Bank, for $635 million in stock.</p>
<p>-- Hewlett-Packard Co will launch a powerful high-end computer and other products Thursday in a bid to regain momentum from rival Sun Microsystems Inc, analysts said.  </p>
<p>-- Novell Inc plans to cut about 15 percent of its European workforce, or about 50 jobs, the Wall Street Journal reported.</p>
<p>-- An initial public offering of Hartford Life Inc priced at $28.25 per share. Hartford Life is a unit of Hartford Financial Services Group.</p>
<p>-- Phillips-Van Heusen posted a first quarter loss of $0.17 per share, compared to a loss of $0.24 in the year-ago quarter.</p>
<p>((--Wall Street Desk 212-859-1730))</p>
